Business Brief -- USLife Corp.:
   Two Subsidiaries' Operations
   Are Going to Be Combined
The company, which said it would retain its Reading
office, would not comment on whether the move would result in
layoffs or charges to earnings.
   Both subsidiaries provide mortgage and disability
insurance and insurance on customers of financial
institutions.
   The company's shares closed at $46.50, down 50 cents, in
trading yesterday on the New York Stock Exchange.